\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He'd been stationed at different lighthouses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. YES. John Watson was his name, mother was called Watson before she was married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was mother's maiden name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Had mother any jobs before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No. No. Then - used to - the reason they got - they got a farm after - they got down to the Trinity buildings where they used to live there as - from the light house people that was provided by the
 light house. And then they runned a farm after that and - when the children kept growing up, 'cos there was ten too, ten children and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother was one of ten children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Children, yes, and they runned a farm you see and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They worked at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she work outside of the house after she was married at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Oh yes, to go out and - help to milk and help on the - with the - you know, doing the - the - the agriculture generally, hay or corn or whatever - or potatoes or anything that was - necessary you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's on her own place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But she didn't go out to work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Go out, no, she didn't go out, no, she never did go out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And she never worked after she had her children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I should
 like to ask you about life at home when you were a child, the time up to when you left school, how many rooms were there in the house at Bosavern Farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh, about five rooms - a kitchen, a - a what do you call it, a kitchen, a dining room and a - per
haps three small bedrooms, rather small. Water was - got from a well. And - that sort of thing, we didn't have any more - and - the ordinary - outdoor - closet, what we call the toilet. Earth closet what we call. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You said there were three bedrooms in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How many rooms downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well two and a dairy, we used to have a - two and one - and the dairy would be in the - back part, like, you know whitewashed out in those days, white - lime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Built on to the back of the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would have been the dairy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And the other room would be a big living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes, yes. And the Cornish range, the old Cornish range used to have then, there was no modern cookers then in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother cooked on the Cornish range?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. And baked cakes and that - she had to bake them on the - put a - iron plate down and cover it over with a hot - cinders and ashes, like - turf and stuff. She'd bake cakes that way, I've seen her do
ing that. And the - the water - the clothes was more or less you had a boiler into a crock what we call in the corner and then you've got to pick fire sticks and - the clothes is all boiled in that every week you know. Boiled with - and used a common soap
 and soda, you didn't use any modern - and - and the - the clothes was boiled and - hanged on a line if you had it, but they more or less lie - used to go on these here - furze bushes and anything like that used to - grow around.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that be called a furnace?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. A furnace, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Downstair}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
 in your house there would be this one big living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Which would be a reception room, parlour, dining room, everything in one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. More or less. But you did get a - a l
ittle - what we called very often - one room as a sitting room, a little room more or less we used to have for - Sundays and sit down in if you like and - a part with a grate in and get a little fire in, different - apart from really the cooking place.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So there were two rooms apart from the dairy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 A parlour and a living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did anyone else besides your parents and brothers and sisters live with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No other relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did mother ever pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, she used to have a girl that came in - they used to have help come in when she got - children coming along.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 A daily help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. And sometime they used to come in as you say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What were her duties then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well to - general clean up and help around you know, buckets had to be washed and - and - general cleaning like when you've got the diary with one or two cows we had and - churn had to be looked
 after and cooking, well my mother did supervise the cooking I suppose,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Any jobs that mother needed help with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she look after the children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you know what hours she would work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 W
ell - there was no fixed - time in those days, you had a kind of a little - wage was very little on those days, there - they'd - they would have their meat and - and - the wages was very low I understand those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They would have food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 While they worked at the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That - that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would she have come regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well yes, like come pretty regularly, yes, really regularly as the churn got bigger and more churn come on and - then - you get a dressmaker come in occ
asionally, perhaps a day or - couple of days to do a bit of dressmaking, you know, altering dresses and - doing - being done for the children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 To go back to the daily help, what did you have to call her, her Christian name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes. It was always
 Jessie or Bessie or whatever she was called, that's right, there was - she was always called by her - say what she was called, Bessie or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How would you get on with this person?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
e always very well you know, they were always kind of jolly and - you know, they'd join in you know, working there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Just like a member of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, yes. There was no - no barriers in those days. It's not like - girls that used to be in service of - of - big houses where there was more or less the lady and so and so and Lady this and that. That was all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 More like a member of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, the - the farming community was - they used to be different to - the larger houses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What would she call your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, she'd more or less call her Mrs Hosken, they always did that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 She wouldn't call her ma'am?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No. No, well they - they didn't used to call them Edwin or Ada like their Christian names was, they more or less call them Mr Hosken, but of course they would call me Wilfred and sometimes different - if -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 About this dressmaker, how often did she come to the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well, just as required like, say perhaps making up nighties and - perhaps - or making the - perhaps the best dresses or - 'cos you had to do
 those days, you couldn't - couldn't afford go in town and buy ready made stuff, not - you'd pick up bit of old garments and they'd come out and - make them up to - suit the - the wearer like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she come from the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 From St Just. She was called Osborn if I remember rightly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she have a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I don't think she did. I think she was a Miss Osborn. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You moved away from there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 In - after eight years at St Just. Then - I took what we call a labour exam then, and me and another chap -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's from school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 From - from St Levan school and - I left school when I was thirteen, I had what we call a labour exam, I was able to go back on the farm.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was the washing done at home or sent out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 All done home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did mother or father make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well mother used to do a lot of mending - especially - nothing unusual to see mother sitting down darning the socks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 She did a lot of mending?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How about shoes, would father mend any shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, father used to do a bit of - tapping, yes, what we call the - putting on the - heels and have these iron - we used to have iron and toe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 plates then. Iron on the heel, heel and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And father would put those on the soles and heels?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did he ever mend your shoes with leather?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, of - oh he'd buy the leather in - in Camborne - in - well - different places, Penzance or anywhere he'd go when ther
e was market and see a piece of leather and perhaps he'd buy a piece of leather and cut it out or - sometimes buy the soles already cut, but - generally used to buy a piece of leather. And they'd be - well by weight and then he used to buy sprigs and - ir
on sprigs. Then used a lot of these -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The springs were what were used to nail them on with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Nail them on with. And then they used to have some studs - what you call for nail - put in the leather to help to keep the leather from wearing, what we call boot studs. Put on toe plates and iron - heel cap - heel irons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 We used to call them protectors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. That's right, and protectors. Yes, used to get protectors too, cards of protectors you can buy them, used to get them. Don't see them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But father used to attend to all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Until the shoes were gone beyond?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Gone beyond, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 We used to have an article called the toe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 boy on which the boot would be placed for mending.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did father use something like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, that's right, yes, a kind of a three - one for heel and one for the - toe, two - for - for the sole part you know and - and one for a large shoe and one for the small shoes, you know, a three part thing it was actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What was that made of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - of iron or steel - or steel more or less, iron.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 To rest the boot or shoe on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Used to soak it in - the leather when it was a bit hard, soak it in a drop of water and tan it, the more you beat it the har
der it go you know. To make it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 To make it stronger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were clothes always new or sometimes second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 hand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Always - well not very often second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 hand, they didn't used to have much second hand stuff in those days nor jumble sales like
 we get now, they used to go in town and - well buy odd - get the sales and buy odds and ends of garments say, odds - remnants what we used to call them. Union dyed shirts and all that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 There were no second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 hand shops but how about passing on from friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well that was done - when you had a family - different family and there was a big family, they'd say, well my boy's grown out of this now will this do for you, and - a little girl be the same thing, frocks and that. There used to be - used
 a lot of white frocks and - girls they used then the white pinafores and all that and - used to go in for a lot of ironing and - you know all that sort of thing, everything used to be done with starch and different - the boys, well they had - they wore t
he ordinary - ordinary - trousers and - corduroys if they get them, shirts and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Corduroy trousers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And sometimes you would have them passed on from others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 From someone else, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And you would pass on?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 As you grew out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was the way second hand clothes came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Well you'd get a best suit you see and you'd have to keep it as the best suit. And if you had two or three brothers sometimes - sometimes if 
the - if - mother couldn't afford a best suit for the two or three boys, see one would go to Sunday school one week, another one'd go Sunday school the next week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where were your clothes usually bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well in Penzance generally, cos that was o
nly - big - big - shopping place. Suits and - mother would great - great - buyer there, she - always dealt with more or less Simpson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 s, who was noted people there, they had branches different places, St Ives, Penzance, Redruth, even she went Simpson when she came to Redruth district to live.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was Simpson}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 s the tailors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was there any special time in the year when clothing was bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not necessary, no, they - they didn't used to spend a lot on clothes in those days, not what yo
u call it like - you more or less you had to have likes of - Olivers and Leonard}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
s perhaps the special boot people they used to go in and have boots, have - had to have decent boot - footwear, we used to have decent footwear, we always did have decent footwear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You used to buy them in the shops in town?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. More or less the socks mum I think used to make some - knit some socks or get someone perhaps a friend to - to get the people she knew like would knit a pair of socks for her sometimes, knit a few pair of socks or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were they always hand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 knitted at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
More or less. More - more - most socks, most of that sort of thing and cardigans or jerseys or something like that for the children was all more or less done with the hand. It's only in the latter part in the war years that we were able to get second}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 hand - what they call clothes come from the Army stores. That's in -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would anything special have been bought at times like Whitsuntide?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, more or less everybody - ye
s, we did - we was always - had - and especially the children, especially the girls, had the special dresses bought for them - like Sunday school dresses and - well they was made of - of kind of a print in a light sort of stuff you know, they was all made
 up from - made up very often like that, that's where the dress}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
maker'd come in sometimes for to - do these sort of things. Special -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 For Whitsuntide?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Whitsuntide. 'Cos the little children used to have the hair ribbons in their hair in those days
 and long hair and - all that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you ever have shoes made for you by a cobbler?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well there was one or two around that did make them, yes - my - Mrs - Mrs Rose, that's - there used to be - what they call the - he had a brother - a
 son - a brother who used to be called Dummy Rowe at Praze, he used to make shoes and boots - for people - but there was - one or two boot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 makers around at that time, used to make - spec - boots and shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there any people who made boots and shoes at St Just or at St Buryan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well there was one - there used to be a boot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 maker who make boots down near - Cripples Hill, that was near St Just, where I used to go for my first Sunday school. I remember having a first Sunday school suit, a velvet suit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would have been made at home or bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh most likely bought, that was bought I think, that was - that velvet suit, I think that was bought somehow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that have been a velvet suit with a lace collar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes. Kid gloves. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that have been made for any special occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well no, that was bought for a special occasion most likely for Sunday school probably.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well not - mu
ch, he wasn't much of an - he never - I never seen him doing any cooking or anything like that way, nor - I never seen him doing a lot, you know. He'd take her a cup of tea I suppose and he could - perhaps he'd dish us up with some porridge and - oatmeal 
and all that sort of thing we used to get in those days, we didn't used to get no cornflakes nor - Shredded Wheat in those days, I don't remember seeing of it, we used to have the ordinary quick Quaker Oats, you know, the old Quaker Oats and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would he help with the cleaning in the house at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Not much. No. They used to have - she used to have the girl - or someone come in to help her that really do that sort of work. She used to do most of the papering herself though, she was rather - good at - at papering.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He didn't help with papering?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Not very much, he had quite enough to do outdoors to do and - and mother - mother did this work unnecessary outdoors because she used to enough quite in - she'd go out and help with the milking an
d - perhaps help tend the - the poultry or the pigs or something like that, but she wouldn't do any - general helping in the fields not a lot unless there was carry - help to carry the corn, what we call making up the corn when its down. 'Cos there was - 
wasn't done - it was all done by hand in those days, all the - machine - machinery was not - not in, it was done with a common scythe what we call and then - then - the reapers came in after, and that would cut the corn down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When the reapers came in would mother have domestic help with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about washing up, would father help with that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I suppose he would do - occasionally, I - we - we children had to do them more or less, I always remember that my father - 
mother used to say to me, take the towel there and wipe those things up for me, and go and get some stick for the boiler and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would father have helped at all with the laying in or lighting of the fires?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well not - necessarily, no, I don't think
 they did like - we - we do, well we more or less had to help to do that, bring in the coal, we - we - we used to get a little bit of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501  coal brought home from the grana}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 ry to Penzance and bring up the coal and they used to get and that - get their own more or less, bring in - bring home the bag stuff, not so much delivery it is now with big lorries like it used - is then.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about household repairs, would father have done any of that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well he was pretty handy in that, always doing - cementing and
 - and building and - rather good at - keeping the hedges - you see, Cornwall is more noted for the stone edges with - they haven't got the fencing and wires like they do up - lot of country you see. See they were more the stone edgings and the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about repairs indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well that was all done - well - he kept things a bit decent, but I don't know, we've had - we've had - fairly decent order.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He could put a nail in, your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, oh yes. They used to do like - like partitions fo
r the cattle, putting partitions in the houses for cattle, keep the cattle separate for milking and all that sort of thing and - putting in cement first but they're more particular on the cement floors now because they've got to have proper drains and all
 that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did he do any improvements to the house, building on or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - he did - in the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did father do any improvements to the house, either inside or out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well he used to keep the roof - the slates - because most al
l the buildings was done with only common - slate in those days, what we call and - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 candle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
 slate, not cut slate like you have now nor - nor these - special tiles, they was all done - most all farm buildings were built with stone and slate, perhaps you'd ge
t a bit of rip or a bit of weakness in a - could wash them in with cement you know and - wash the walls, but we used to have a - use a lot of lime - in those days, square - get the rock lime and quench it down and lime out shelters and piggeries and - all
 had to be done with lime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Could you get the lime locally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, used to go in to Penzance and get the hundredweights or half hundredweights what you wanted of rock lime and boil it to put it in your containers and boil it down, you'd boil - you'd
 have to be careful with it, because if you get it in your eyes you - very -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So father could put a slate back or do general repairs?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Well we used to have to general repainting you know, and keep anything like that sort of thing, puttying -
 a bit of putty in the windows and painting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 This small holding that you lived at, that would have been rented would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh - all - all - all the places that father lived on before the - he come to Treloweth in about 1916 I think, something like
 that, was all rented. He did eventually buy the place at Treloweth after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So keeping the house in repair himself, that would have been a duty the landlord would have expected of him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And the fences had to be kept up and the manure, the - they u
sed to claim for - if they use any manure, special - organic manures, except the ordinary farm manure, they used to what you call the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501  un}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
exhausted manure, they used to claim for that if they'd had kept - saved the bills for it you see, and any re - any - unnecessary repairs would fall upon the land - the tenant, so that - he would have to pay for to have that repaired if he left it go in d
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 lapidation what we call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was in the agreement?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Agreement, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Who would have been the landlord, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - the - he comes under Robartes and - those are landlords but he - they more or less sent - he came under this - two or three of them came under local farmer that - they were able to buy their land and then they used to let it out you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's from the Agar Robartes from Bodmin?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes, that up here - or this part up here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did father help at all with the children, did he help mother with the dressing or undressing of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I don't think so, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about bathing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No, well - we didn't have any bathrooms then, not - I don't think - the - 'til latter years, we used to have the ordinary - why - tray what we call a wood tray or else a galvanized bath we used to stand up in or -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 A galvanized bath or else the wooden wash bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be brought into the big kitchen would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, brought into kitchen, that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would there be special days for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, we general
ly used to have the weekends more or less, I don't think we would have - remembering having more than a bath once a week what we call. You'd have clean changes every week, we'd always have our clean changes what we called.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be after the bath time would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, that's right. And - we used to wear the - didn't used to wear so much - pyjamas as they do now, you used to have a nightdress or night shirt or something like that. That - that's all. Never used to have no electric like blankets 
in those days, or anything, no, no, we had oil lamps for - for ordinary lighting. Candle - candles, we used - I remember the old candle - lanterns, used to put a candle in a lantern, have an oil lantern what they could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 carry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you'd probably bath on Saturdays ready for your clean things on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did father ever read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, he was a great - reader - more or less and they - you started cooking on Sunday mornings sometimes and - he'd read the Bible to us and we'd have a bit of sing-song, something like that, unless we went to church or chapel. Sunday morning. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did he ever read anything else to you,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - we - we - I don't - we didn't have time sometime for the morning prayer or anything like th
at, but occasionally we would have grace, perhaps on Sunday sometimes and - more or less you - you - you was called in to a - kind of good behaviour, you - if you wanted your bottom tanned you'd have bottom tanned if you was - wasn't allowed to get into t
he mischief they get in today because - you wouldn't be allowed to get away with it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What would you have done -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Girls too - I remember my sisters when they grew up, they had to be in a certain time, nine o'clock and that 'cos it was late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 For what reason would father give you a tanning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - well - perhaps you'd be out striking matches or - carrying matches, perhaps starting a bonfire somewhere, or doing something you didn't ought to do and - and endanger - endanger }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501 t}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 ricks or - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mischief that was dangerous?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Dangerous. You know. And - if you was asked a question and - some - and you told him a lie or something like that, you were liable to get a tanning for that, he wouldn't - stand for being told lies yo
u know. And we was never have to answer mother back nor father back, we was never left to do it, he would - and if you was asked to do anything for your mother father would say now didn't your mother ask you to do so and so, and you knew - you knew - knew
 what - that - what that meant, you went and go and done it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Father would always support mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 More or less in that way of things. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did he ever tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes, yes, he'd tell us stories, especially of his 
old days, of the different horses and the dogs and what things - of things that happened - and different - things. When he used to go - he used to go on Scilly Isles, help on the potatoes and the flower farm occasionally when he was a boy and - well used 
t
o do horse riding, yes, and - and they used to keep - their family before he was married used to keep race horses, used to have the old Buryan races what they call, and used to keep the horses and - breed - breed horses and - and you know colt, bring on y
oung - young stock and - he used to delight in breaking in - horses, he was very good - very good man at breaking horses, young horses. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What sort of races did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well the old - type - what we get - get down here today, not - never call
ed the point to point, but - no, just a farmers - what they call the races used to get. They'd run down St Buryan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 In the farmers fields?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, in the farmers fields. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And the various farmers would bring the horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, brin
g their - bring the horses there, that's right. I don't know if they used to have any bets and any - no bookmakers in those days, they may have a bet on themselves, a bottle of whisky or something - I couldn't say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Father would tell you stories really from his memory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did he ever take you out without mother like for walks or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, used to take us to Sunday school, I can remember me going to Sunday school with father, when man is - say, well mam is getting the dinner we'll go to Sunday school this morning or go to church or chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He would take you to church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. And mother - mother was a great - they was Wesleyans in those days, more or less, they wasn't church people, and mother used t
o play, when she was a girl in the Senned chapel, she played the organ for the chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother used to play the organ at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. I can always remember and she'd - she used to have - she had her there with the old organ, we used to h
ave the old Corn - the old farm - the; cottage organ you know and - she would sit down sometimes of a Sunday and - we'd have a bit of sing-song, mother would play a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16143970\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 hymn or two, she wasn't - couldn't play nothing classical but - we'd have a sing-song and e
specially if the aunties or others came in sometimes I mean or - gathered round, have the Christmas carol and - all those sort of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 A sort of American organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 American organ we used to call with little stops on it, with bellows and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Which chapel would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 At Sennen. At Sennen. The old - the last chapel in Sennen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Methodist chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, in those days, yes. We used to have old preacher come there, never - they didn't used to come round with the collars and ti
es and a white stiff collar like you do now you know, one fellow used to come there, he used to have a open neck shirt, you know a proper old - you know - country man, but - there was - real - good preachers in those days, they was really preach from the 
- from the heart, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 If mother was out would father look after you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes, if there was the - well more or less supervise, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you have any tasks that you had to carry out regularly at home to help your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - we used to have to milk, help to milk, and help to feed the pigs. Now we had - we wasn't allowed to linger on the way home from school of a evening because we had to get back to see that - to help to go on with the milking and the eve
ning work, what we call. That was cleaning out the sheds and - cow sheds and - all that sort of thing. Sometimes we - we used to keep young bullocks, you'd put them in a big - house, and they used to - put a lot of loose straw and hay or furze, we used to
 cut a lot of ferns in those day, on - on the - from the waste ground, and put in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You used to cut ferns, what would that be for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Fern - that would be putting in for help to - help the - help the straw and that, 'cos you'd want the straw more or
 less for the cattle for eating and that. But any surplus put in under for their feet to keep them clean, and pigs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be put in the cows houses and the pigs houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, in the - yes, and not - not everywhere we could get it but lots of
 places round was - you'd get this ferns, cut the ferns and dry them. Makes good - manure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 There'd be a lot of ferns around on the common land I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes. Then we used to have - rabbits used to be pretty plentiful around, we used to go 
to have a - after the - corn harvest over go out to have a bit of sport sometimes for a few days - with the ferrets and guns and dog, and go out with nets, put nets down in front of the holes, I remember, and catch the rabbits, and then - used to save the
 skins in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So while you were still at school you used to go out to catch rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Of an evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well yes, go out with the - father'd go out with the guns sometimes stalking in the evening after he'd catched up his wor
k and we'd go out and look over edge and catch rabbits sitting and grazing you know. I've know him - to fire a gun and hit two and I believe once he hit three - hit two or three one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He was a good shot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Rather a good shot, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you do any other tasks besides milking and doing out the pibs and cows houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well trimming edges a bit sometimes, trimming - because they had to be kept trimmed back otherwise they'd go out in the ditches, and keep the fields clear. And - but the old 
type of - manure and that - used to take up the - have a shovel - father did years ago, dig up the ditches right around close to the stone edges and make a drain like around so the water'd drain away better, and - that used to be put in a pile in the fiel
d, in the corner of a field or in the middle of a field, and then the farm manure was put on and mixed all up together with that and makes kind of a rotted manure - to go over the ground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would clean out the ditches for drainage and putting the contents in for helping with the manure?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you continue to do these tasks after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Oh yes, that's more so. Yes. Yes. Help to - ride - take the horses with - on - they used to keep horses, no tractors in tho
se days and - ponies, and - have horses, you generally have two. I have seen - of an occasion of three working in a - in a - ploughing, when they had heavy ploughing, and he used to have three whips and they used to have a double whip, what they call the 
v
antage whip, the - the - the smaller horse or the younger horse would get that advantage, the - the two horses would be pulling on one side of it and one horse on the other one. It was called a vantage whip, and - they used to - you - used ropes for steer
ing you see, you'd walk behind and - you use the plough and - I learnt to plough and you had chisel for breaking up ground.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you do ploughing while you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I - not necessary, used to - used to lot - they had - they used to us
e the chain harrow a lot, we had a lot of dairy cows, used to lease a - like what they call a chain harrow, a sort of thing with - like a chain links, and you put over the ground without earth in the ground we would knock all the cow dung and all that sor
t of - and then if you put - fresh manure out, after they'd been there about a while, they'd - they'd put this chain harrow to keep it from killing the grass.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 To scatter it a bit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Scatter it. But now they got the modern - dung spreaders now, of 
course they can scatter it round with - without - taking it out - we used to take it out in a cart, the manure, and dig it out in piles, then you had to go with the muck - with a couple of forks and spread it around thinly. That was always done. It was qu
ite a little jobs on those farms that you had to do, and always kept your hands full.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your brothers and sisters do odd jobs at home after school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well the girls used to be indoors more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They'd help mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And your brother George?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well he - he was home and then he went - and Charlie, but George was the only one that actually launched out from the family, he went to drive - when he came up - after - when he got of age after he left school, went to dr
ive for a taxi people and motor people, he went St Ives and Penzance, and then eventually he went to - America, in General Motors.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did he have to do any of these little chores like you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes he - and especially when we got the milk round, 
he used to go out with the milk in - we didn't used to have cans in those days, and the milk used to be cooled - used to - cool it off and - cool - and then taking out in - buckets, hand buckets with the pint measures, open measures, there's no - bucket -
 bottles like they've got these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did he do this while he was still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. At school, that's right. Well all of us did, we all - we all did after that 'til - 'til we - well that's - that's when I'm talking about, the latter part now, 1915/16 now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that be before you went to school you'd have to do some of that would you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well we had to do the milking - before, yes. Well most all boy - children could milk before they could go to school more or less, more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And they carrying out of the milk, would you have done that in schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well you see, in - in the farm - before - at Bosanketh, St Buryan we went to a dairy - a - a factory where they manu - manufactured into butter and cream. That's the St Levan factory what they call. That's the surplus from the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So that while you and your brother helped on the farm your sisters would help mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Andy sewing or - washing or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They would help mother with sewing and washing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Ye
s. They had to come out and help to plant potatoes when we put the potatoes in, which had to be done by hand you see, there's machines and - and when -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 This would be done after school would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 More or less, except - on the weekends when they do
n't go to school, and then you go out then when the potatoes and that and any other crops had to be marketed and brought in they would help - assist on that, help with the buckets or anything like that. Especially on the corn harvest, you carry the sheave
s of corn in and bring them into the - when they stack 'em in and make hand mou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501  and we call and Irish mous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 . Now the - the different in the Cornish - hand mous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
 you would make 'em up so that they'd come up and then you would turn the butts upside down, keep the rain way. But}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501  the hand - the - the Irish mou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
 made by kind of a knew, you'd get up and - they'd hand the sheaves up and they'd come - work them in by the knee, and build them up then, they - they - the hand mous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501  run about a sixty-four to the mou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 sse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501  and the - but the - Cornish - Irish mous}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
 which - the Cornish standard they - they used to do in case they wanted to sell it, same as when the farmer was going to move and want to sell any surplus mous}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 se}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 , they run about a hundred and sixty sheaves to the mou}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11546085\charrsid11542501 sse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
. Then - but then - all this was brought in after to a big hay rick or stack, and then they had no big - coverings in like - in those days like they've got what we call them - these here - specially built barns now, they got - used to - no Dut
ch barns, they all done by - and they used to use the - the straw thatching. Used to cut some reeds if you had any wet ground sometimes up to the moors, we could cut the - what they call the rushes. They would make lovely - thatch for going over the corn.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was your house thatched?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No, neither one, I don't think ever I lived in thatched ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you sell that straw for thatching then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Their - sometime they get - grow the wheat and that sort of thing, they'd sell it for thatching. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did the older children help the younger with the things they found difficult, like dressing or eating?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh well that was all - yes, more or less - automatic. Yes, come down and - the things that they was wearing as they got too small was ha
nded down to the next one and so on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would the older ones help the younger ones to dress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Oh yes, that was - more or less the - recognised -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you have to help in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When I was - I always remember when I was on the - firs
t when I had two or three brothers and sisters the mother and father used to go - Penzance of a Thursday, they used to go here early of the morning sometimes when they killed their pork -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Thursdays was market day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Market day it was, and they - t
hey'd go early in the morning and take the pigs they had killed and all wrapped in white - sheets, used to keep them, and they used to go off in the cart and then they'd say, now you - look after the children and give them their tea and put them to - the 
s
mallest to bed before we come home, if we're late. And they'd bring home all the groceries and then for a week's - supply you see. You get a local baker sometimes come in and might be local butcher but - once a week or something like that, but they used t
o have get most of the groceries - weekly, mother used to get - I always remember up to her last, used to have a fortnights groceries from Lipton\rquote 
s, always have - you never go in and but she would always have a quarter of tea or a bit of sugar, always had h
er fortnight's groceries in. And she used to - find fault with people racing up and down, always on the - on the race she'd say for - for a ha'porth of this and ha'porth of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 She bought her goods in bulk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 In bulk. Yes. Yes. Yes. But we alway
s look out for - when they used to come home from Penzance I remember - 'cos used to - the - the shopkeepers, most of them used to give children - give 'em - if you had a nice order, they'd send home a little packet of sweets. Packet of sweets. So - used 
to look forward to this packet of sweets.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's when mother came home from the market?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did the younger children help the older ones in any ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they did, yes, I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Can you think of any ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - you know,
 nothing you can say from - washing them or - combing their hair - combing their hair was a big item in those days because your hair was kept longer and - brushing and combing hair was quite a problem in those days and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They all had long hair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Had it braided I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. I remember father used to - always - that was father - remember when - the boys used to come out and father said now, better have your hair cut tonight. And - we'd always have our hair cut - trimmed, fath
er - I don't remember ever going to a barber when I was a boy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Father used to cut your hair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes. That was his - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 It wouldn't have been what we call a basin cut would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He trimmed it properly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh you wouldn't have much left, you was like a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Trimmed it well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
You looked like a convict. But he used to do a good job, I mean it looked tidy I'll say that. And then mother would say, now come on - go and wash your feet, you feet's dirty and - then
 she said, now - cut your nail - come on we'll have - have the session then, we'd have our finger and toenails cut. All this.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you'd all take it in turn to have a foot bath?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were you expected to go to bed at a certain time in your schooldays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well we was all very reasonable time, yes. Yes. We had - never very late. No. Well there was nothing amuse us more than a few dominoes as - or something like that or paper or going - ring boards you know. There was no card 
playing, we was never allowed to play cards, we never had any sort of daily papers, nothing like that to read, and - we might get a comic in and out and mother - the - the only thing we ever got - might get brought home from ST Just was the Cornishman and
 - the Sunday - Sunday Companion, something like that, well that's generally the only papers we ever seen then. There was no - nothing about sex nor nothing in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You used to take the Cornishman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was the Penzance paper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, and mother used to - had for all the years and - West Britain, we still have it now, I suppose I - I suppose we've been having the West Britain for as long as can remember. Yes. Yes, it's up here, well used to be Cornishman when we was down St Bur
yan way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did mother or anyone else put you to bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - they used to tuck us in more or less but we didn't have - tucking in like they do now sometime. I - I think well - now you see here's a candle and - off you go. And you take - if you - it
 was cold well you'd have an hot water bottle occasionally we used to have the old stone bottles in those days I remember an old stone bottle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Stone jars?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No - no rubber jars, no. But - we have - I have memory up in the - ordinary brick you know
 and putting that in the warm and carrying that wrapped in a cloth. Very - keep the heat a long time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 A warmed brick in the oven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And wrapped it in a cloth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, otherwise it'd be too hot you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And used that to heat the bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right. Yes. Old bed-warmer, I have seen them but we didn't used to use them, I don't remember using them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you remember what age you put yourself to bed or did you always since you can remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - no, I
've always - just - I don't remember as any - you know particular times nor - when you was tired and if you wanted to go when you were sent to bed you had to go to bed so that was the only thing, and when they was tired of having you down - whether you wa
s tired or no you had to go to bed. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you share the bedroom or the bed with anyone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, was generally about two boys or perhaps - was perhaps two or three in a bed. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You had two bedrooms you said at first didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So two or three boys in a bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well then there was - if we didn't have a bed sometimes you get a - what they call the pillows or - bed lay - overlay on the floor sometimes you know, laying on the floor if we didn't have a proper - w
e never used to be short of bedclothes but we used - always - I always remember like - never been so short like you've seen some. We was never so poor we couldn't have a bit of bedding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You always had bedding but sometimes the bed would be made up on the floor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Yes. The food was nothing - wouldn't call like you get now, you don't get a lot of these fancy buns or cakes, we used to get proper heavy homemade cake and - well - you know, plenty of eggs and plenty of farm milk, and all that sort of thing. But -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
The sleeping arrangements for the whole family, would that have been the children all in one room and the parents in one or would some of the children be in with the parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well it's like the younger - very younger ones can be 
in a cot, or some of that sort of thing but - they more or less they - when they got - big enough when we had two rooms, well the little - little - girls would be in one room and the boys in another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You told me that you used to bath Saturdays, that would be done in the kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 More or less, that's the only way you could do it, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Once a week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Then once a week that would have been the time for the clean clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where did the family have their meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well we used to have a proper dinner table you know, one of the - the - Corn - big old Cornish tables, used to all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 In the big kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, used to hold - perhaps ten or a dozen see sit around - fo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7684754\charrsid11542501 r}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 ms and - have a big long form inside sometimes and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You sat on forms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Long form like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 With legs at each end?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. And back to it sometimes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I'm trying to think what the proper name for that is.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Settle or something I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Or wooden forms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, wooden form.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 As opposed to chairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You wouldn't have chairs to sit to table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No. No. Father'd have the old armchair, always remember our father having the old armchair, and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Father and mother had old armchairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you actually have a settle in the living room back against the wall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they used to have a settle more or less up near the stove what we called it, little settle that used to sit up - perhaps mother or on
e or two - or father or somebody be sitting up around - into the - near the fireplace, 'cos some of the old fireplaces had a proper - seat in beside the fire like we call -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did yours have that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well there's only one place I remember, but - gener
ally you have a settle, what we call a two seater thing with a wood back to it that you could draw round where you wanted to like, see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Something like a wood }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7684754\charrsid11542501 settee}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 With no padding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Very rough, very hard you see. Don't get the modern - studio couch and like we've got now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there any occasions when you ate in another room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - I - I think it was more or less - I don't think we did actually, always most meals was - from the kitchen - from the dining room what
 we used to call 'em, 'cos - then sometimes you get a pantry where you done a lot of washing up and kept some of the things likes of - storage of food and that well - that was apart from the kitchen or - what we called dining room, but then the sitting ro
om was kept as a sitting room, you only used it at special occasions like Sundays or - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You used it to sit in on Sundays but you never did use it to eat in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, no, it was never used - it was more or less kept - different to
 - it was never used as - everyday nor - it wasn't a common room, it was always kept for - special occasion, anybody come in like and visitors.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Reception room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Reception. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You didn't eat there even at Christmas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not - very seldom, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where did mother cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well from the Cornish range generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 In the big living room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Used to have the old - oil stoves in those days you know more or less, the Primus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The Cornish range was for baking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But if she hadn't got a fire you would use the oil stove?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's with the two burners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. And they used to get a Primus - Primus really after it come on - later on, but I don't suppose that was in the early}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7684754\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 part, but 
I always remember the Primus's. And then the - the lamp - the lighting was all done by an hurricane lamp or else - oil lamps. They did get - eventually get to this Primus - well this Aladdin lamps which is very good lights. But we used to use the hurrican
es - for outdoors you know, the light - the hand hurricane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The hurricane lantern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, for - no - no electric lights there weren't. Some people did - eventually come - years come by get - where they couldn't get the electric in they used to have
 what they call - a self - generating plants. That was done by a farmer who's got a bit - be able to - to do it and had the money you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That wouldn't be in the early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When was breakfast eaten at home in the early days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 W
ell first thing in the morning, after - you may have a cup of tea sometimes or something like that, but you more or less have - that would be after you had done your milking and the - things is ready prepared for - for - just before you go to school an al
l that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would all have breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Yes. That would be more or less a regular thing and be all together sort of, unless someone was detained with a sick animal or something like that or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 After the milking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What members of the family would be present then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well, all, mother and father, yes, all. Yes. Yes. Except for the baby or - sick, child - might be more - some more upstairs but they'd be brought down and dressed later, yes. The essential thing was to get 
the milking done - and - get the children to school, that was the first things in the morning, that was more essential, and then the other little things would come in rotation afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother would deal with the little ones after you'd gone to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What did you usually eat for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - porridge, you get the - sometimes, what they call the Quaker Oats and - I remember, I used to get the ordinary bread, plenty of bread and - cake, your homemade cakes you know and - bit of cream occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that be for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, that's right, the porridge and the bread and butter and marmalade or jam, homemade jam, very often homemade again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What would you drink at breakfast time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well ordinary - just tea. Didn't used to see a lot of coffee in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So that would be porridge?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Well we -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Bread and butter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Always had plenty of milk with our porridge and all that, eggs, you'd get a egg fried sometimes, you ge
t a boiled egg sometimes if you fancied it. Boiled egg you see and break the shell and eat it from the shell and - egg cup.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you have anything different for breakfast on certain days like Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I don't think we did really. Change today
 I suppose toast - might have a bit of toast or something like that, but - used to get - see used to get fish down here, buy your fish in bulk more or less, and - it'd be put in storage like, and used to have - hang up - used to have say sometimes the pig
 been killed and you have a bit of ham or pork and - sometimes and all that sort of thing and - used up then - when we had pigs killed, if we had some of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5795947\charrsid11542501 fal}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501  we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5795947\charrsid11542501 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 d get that fried up for dinners, but not for breakfast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What would you normally eat for dinner then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - stew, we used to have a lot of stew and dumplings and - sort of - that sort of thing and - pasties, Cornish pasties was the old time - we used to get. For - for - bit of fried bacon, perhaps fried eggs sometimes, fried potatoes is qui
te - lot of - too - fried potatoes, we used a lot of - most all families used to eat potatoes, a lot of potatoes, yes, and used to get a - quite a bit of stew what we called with dumplings and all that sort of thing. Rice puddings all that, made up with o
r
dinary rice and then - boiled with water and then - milk - milk and a bit of sugar with it. Syrup was used quite a bit. Quite - you know the ordinary - especially the dark syrup - was there for sweetening you know, puddings and all that. Custard. And - us
e
d to make quite a bit of junkets in summertime, that was sort of the milk done with whey you know, the kind of the - milk with - junket, that was used for afterwards. Used to have - well it was quite a treat, we only used to get that Sundays, very often, 
jellies, made up jellies, you'd - buy the - jelly and make a jelly. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about teatime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well that was done with bit of buns and - used to have - regular tarts is going, like apple tart and blackberry, rhubarb tart, pick a lot of blackberries
, we used to go out and gather blackberries, make blackberry jelly and - mother used to - do a lot of preserving what we called like - we did - they used to - didn't used to buy a lot of jams. Bring home a bit of marmalade, used to have the old Dundee mar
malade and - bit of the syrup what we call, the Lyles syrup and all that, barring that - almost all that sort of thing was homemade. Orange and apples and all that, and things like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5795947\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
of the day would you have your lunch or dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5795947\charrsid11542501 Oh well, around - around twelve}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 ish as we was home from school and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The family had lunch at about twelve to one, what time would tea have been taken?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - generally after - evening work was done really, the really the main-tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 After milking would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, after the evening work what we call the evening milking and - because we didn't - work - then father never did encourage - a late - he did keep the thing as regular, he'd have a fairly - constituent - time, he'd milk in the morn
ings at regular - regular time, and in the evening of a regular time. You find the cattle - respond better to the milk because - a cow - especially summer time when they're - got extra milk, if they're no relieved then they - then kind of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They had to keep regular hours for the livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And your family meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
More or less, that was for - for that simple reason that they - you were looking at this the - the milking had to be done at regular intervals. You can't milk a cow six o'
clock in the morning then milk him three o'clock in the afternoon. You can do it occasionally if you have to go away somewhere sometimes you'd have to stretch a point but then - on the regular generally average you would - you would try to keep them balan
ced.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you had tea that would be perhaps about six when milking was finished, would that be a high tea with anything cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, generally - probably if mother had a rasher of bacon or something - a few sausages or a few - baked - if the pig
s been killed or something else, you - stuffed - pudding skins or - something like that or - you know, something like that, we wouldn't have - not the - you don't have like a kind of fish and chips or - we'd fry - we - we used to fry up a lot of chips now
,
 well you - you didn't used to fry a lot of chips in those days. It - like fried potato, bit of fried potato and egg probably. But generally they came under a bit of heavy - heavy bun like what used to make now, a bit of heavy cake or - perhaps a - cream 
and jam sometimes if you had - summertime we had plenty of cow come in you would have a bit of extra cream and then we'd have a dish of cream and then - you would always have a nice cream - cream tart or cream and jam or -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you have anything different on Sundays for your Sunday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - it was generally - tart was baked for - I told you, and jellies before. Jellies and tarts. We'd have something different - we used to have - have - have bread and butter or something catch up meals, or bun
 or - something like that, you wouldn't have - Sunday meal was generally made up of a tart, you didn't have tarts in the week, not unless you have blackberry tart sometimes when blackberries were plentiful, and fruit was going.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your mother or father bake their own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Used to occasionally, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not always?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not always, but they did bake a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she make her own jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she bottle any fruit or vegetables?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, she bottled a lot of fruit in - and do her own pickles, pickled onions you know and all that and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 She did pickled onions, would she have done any other kind of pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I - she might pickle a bit of cabbage occasionally, yes, but - pickled onions was generally the more or less.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What kind of fruit would she bottle besides blackberries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well, she might get a - plum or two sometimes or something like that. I don't think the apples was plentiful so we didn't bottle them, I don't think - ever remember them bottled very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you grow any gooseberries?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Or blackcurrants?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Grew some blackcurrants, used to make them into jam and - and preserve them and jam too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she make any wine or any medicines for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they ha
ve - they have - what they call the - hawthorn, the - what we call that there - elderberry. Yes. Wine. Yes. And she has made cider from apples you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was the elderberry wine for medicine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 More or less, yes. Yes, that was for - for -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 For colds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, colds, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was any beer brewed for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No, father being a teetotaler, non-smoker.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother would make the cider would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I think occasionally, have occasionally but - the blackberry wi
ne - she made blackberry wine, made from the blackberry you know. And sloe wine, pick the sloes. Sloe wine, so that was given more or less some medicine in case - for - used for more or less a medicine too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So the sloe wine and the elderberry wine were medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Med - medicine. Medicine. Medical. Medical. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did father or mother grow their own vegetables and fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they grew most of their - and they used to have - if they had a little bit of garden they would grow a few goosebe
rries, blackcurrants, used to like a few - and rhubarb was very plentiful, most everybody had rhubarb in those days. And - grow a few - plant cabbages and - a few carrots and - more or less, and turnips, turnip was big then. Mangolds were more or less for
 the cattle - was for horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You grew mangolds for the feeding of the livestock?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your parents buy any fruit or vegetables?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they have done - fresh, yes, occasionally, but - a lot of their - main crop, like potatoes 
and that was grewn on the farm - growed on the farm. All right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you would have potatoes anyway because you grew them on the farm, did they ever buy any tinned or dried vegetables or fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - no, I don't think we never used to see a lot o
f dried fruit, tinned fruit. Used to bring home tins of corned beef and something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Livestock for the family, you kept pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And keep - keep a - always kept a few fowls, and a few chickens.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You did keep hens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Get a few eggs, I don't think ever remember - a farm without having a few fowls.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about goats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, we didn't - no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Who looked after them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Never - only - never went in for sheep much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Who looked after the hens and pigs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - we did between us and mother used to go out and - and - sometimes. Mother used to go out to collect the eggs. Herself. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So the whole family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. More or less the general - idea it was you know. I used to have to go out the lime - do the li
ming very often, and clean - clean out the - cleaning out and do the liming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So each did according to his age and ability?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Age and ability.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How many times a week did you eat meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - not - being a - having - being - having - being
 able having a chance of get a rabbit on the farm - the - I think we more or less - we used to be able to get a rabbit or two. And used to kill - well nothing for you to go out if you wanted to-go out, if you run short you'd go out and kill - a fowl, a fo
wl that stopped laying or - have roosters or young -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would kill a fowl from your own farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, sometimes we'd get - more or less that would be - that's the Sunday treat if you get a fowl or a chicken for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you ever eat butcher's meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well yes, there were - we used to quite get - my mother - when we was up - come up this way to live - particularly more - remember buying this fifteen or sixteen pound rump from Mr Pooly, Pooly the - you know, and then you'd have a nice cut
ting from it you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was from the local butcher?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Buy in bulk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Well that - for the weekend joint what we call. And - if we're going to chapel or church and we have a friend come home with us or something like that we always have a beef supper, have a bit of beef supper we used to look forward to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So that would be on Sundays mostly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you lived out at St Just and St Buryan did the butcher bring meat around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes, they 
used to come around. I remember the butcher came around - I had a lot of warts at St Just and the butcher came around and he said, pity you got all those warts, he said, when I'm not looking at you take a piece of beef off the cart and rub it in your - fi
ngers and bury it in the ground. And you know, fortnight after he come and all my warts was gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So they used meat to cure your warts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they ever have tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. We didn't have much tinned meat because you - you more or 
less had your - your own pigs and they used to kill a pig and - used to have a bit in stock any bit of bacon or something, a bit of - salted pork.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 It wasn't available here very much in those days was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Except corned beef?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you ever get some extra meat such as rabbit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But that wouldn't have been from poaching would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No, no, that's from your own farm - that's from - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was fairly frequent?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you remember seeing your mother having less food so that the family could have more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - sometimes I used to think so. I remember one afternoon I was - she was eating some jelly that was left over, and she's - she said, well you can have what's left, sh
e was cutting - they were giving away on this here - spoon out of the basin, I said, oh, won't be none left for me in a minute. And she said, here, go on, eat it. But you see I never enjoyed it because I found afterwards more in than I thought it was you 
k
now. I always remember seeing all this - mother would always give you and - if - my brother George was - he always he suffered bil - bilious attacks, and - if he wasn't feeling very good she would cook something different, a bit of toast or something diff
e
rent meal like for him, and he would sit back at the table and have this different you know. But - normally, if - we all had to eat what was given to us otherwise you would do without. And - the whole problem would be - used to be, the one that eat the mo
st soup will have the most beef.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your father have more than the other members of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I don't think so, he was never a greedy man, no, not that way, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were you allowed to talk during meals or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No - we was never al
lowed to - come - be un - unruly at meals, never talk with your mouth full and all that. I remember going over to my granny's when I was very small and I wasn't sitting up to the table properly and granny said, now come on, put your shoulders back and sit
 
up properly, you know, granny, always remember saying that to me, you know. And I went to stay - vis - visit my auntie in Lon - in London and I went out - in the street you see, never buttoned me coat up properly and I was putting my glove on - button my 
coat and aunty say now - you must properly for to go out, you're not home in the country now you know. You see, she - she always laughed and giggled over it, but - see - the - the different places got different - atmospheres and rules if you understand -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you would be allowed to talk but not with your mouth full?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - no, you wouldn't be allowed - if you was told to stop or is you was - being un - necessary, you'd be told to stop, - and - if you were told - if you - Molly, my wife's father, us
ed to tell her, now, he said, if you can't behave yourself you'd better get up and - leave the table, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked or did you have to eat a bit of everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - you more or less - hav
e your share, you - if you'd have - fried potatoes or whatever dish you be dished up, and if you felt you could have a bit more and bit more there you could have it and - you'd have your bit of afters what you would like after - sometimes you might be luc
ky and have two afters, you may have rice pudding and stewed tart, and you could have which you wanted to, but it was very often rice pudding was the preference and that's what you'd get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What was your parents attitude if you left some food uneaten on the plate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, sometimes it was saved for you again, but occasionally it was given to the dog but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So it was never wasted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Wasted. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 If there was something on the table you wanted like the salt, could you ask someone to pass it t
o you or did you have to wait until it was offered to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well you'd ask for it. Well yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Could you ask for a second helping?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well you'd - well sometimes, can you have a bit more of that, anymore - anybody want anymore? If mum says
, a bit more left, who wants a bit more, well - somebody who fancied it could have a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were you expected to hold your knife and fork in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh you had to - yes, you was given them to use, you wasn't allowed to eat with your knife '
cos - that was - could - you were never - wouldn't sit down at the table and eat with your knife because you wasn't - allowed to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And you had to sit up to table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Sit up straight properly reasonably. And you had to sit close to the table 
'cos otherwise some would be dropping down and - and you'd be told to sit up close otherwise you were leaving the stuff all on the floor or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Sit up close to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Could you bring toys or a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No. No. That was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When could you leave the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - if you wanted to leave you generally asked them, can - can I leave the table or can I - I've finished now and I want to go to school, I want to go and do something, well you would
 ask - you - you didn't - you didn't make a practise of getting up and just come and go to the table as you wanted to, it was never - it was never recognized at that. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You could ask and be allowed to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did all the family sit at the table for the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Generally, yes. But - the unfortunate part motor was always dishing up by the time she'd dished up there'd be all boys finished so she would sit more or less on her own - on her own you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So mother would serve you all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 More or less.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And have hers after you'd finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Unless one of the girls was helping sometimes too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 If one of the girls was helping sometimes she would sit with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you always have the same places at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Generally. Yes. Generally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother served the meal always did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Generally, yes, with help of her - daughters and - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were you served in any special order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, no, not necessary, no, no, I don't think so. No preference was no preferences no that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother would just go round the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
