e that I had to go home on the farm when I could perhaps gone in the Country School or somewhere and got - got a higher education, but I wasn't able to go because we didn't have the money and didn't have the - we had to work on the farm. But - I - worked 
hard in the war and went down to - the quarries - in the war, and saved up the money to buy my own lorry and - second hand one, then I went on the council and - contract for twenty years, and got out of it. And -
