Well they did, yes, truthfulness and - that, and respect. And they - they said - my - they say, well you - if you haven't got no manners you can look - you can be - tidy and - keep yourself tidy and - you know wha
t I mean, they used to - try and keep you tidy, and - mother used to be doing - I've heard - well you don't think nothing about it now but I've seen down darning - the elbows gone out of your - jumper or darn your socks or doing things or ironing your shi
r
t - but - the shirts was ironed and put properly that they was fit to wear you know, you go out tidy and - if the collar was wore you would have them changed and all that sort of thing and - you won't be allowed to go around in rags if it was possible to 
keep you otherwise and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they have any special ambitions for you?
