No. No I don't think so, we more or less - I - the funny thing that - when I settled up mother's estate ninety-four and we went in, four of us was on the secretaries and - Mr Thomas said - so and so and so and so, I said well we have agreed t
o do so and so. He said, never seen a boy - a family like you in your life, he said, all pull together. And we always made that point that we always - pull together. We didn't find - we know - we - we - had our differences but we agreed before we - we nev
e
r move - go and make a - a mess of things. No. The old story - of a - mouse that had a bit of cheese, and - they couldn't abide it, two mice you see, so they got another one come in and they go on - kept putting it on the scales and nibble a bit off - nib
ble a bit off 'til there's no more left, so they - neither one of 'em had anything so I think it's a good story attached to that.
