\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Can you remember what you spent it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - we didn't used to have a lot to spend it on, you had - buy a few sweets or few marbles or something like that, we didn't used to spend it - we never used to buy any - thing like -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Sweets or marbles or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after her house or family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No relations or friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 If your mother was ill or confined to bed how did she manage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
They used to have a lady come in to look after her - called the - keeper in what they call when they had the babies or something like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Something like a midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Midwife, s
omebody - some of the ladies used to go round - one or two of them, old Mrs Blewett and one or two I remember the old days, it wouldn't be a - proper nurse but they was kind of a - old nurses but old people what you call an old people what goes round and 
do that kind of thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Someone experienced in confinements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was what happened when your younger brothers and sisters were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 This lady came and looked after mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did she stay in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Yes. Mm. I remember call - she was called Mrs Blewett she was. Yes. From St Just. And there was another one called, an old lady, she's an old lady called - Mary Pendray, Mary, she - she died in the - in the work
house at - eventually at - Penzance. Called Mary Trewavas. Nice old soul, she was down from birth for my mother - other mother's sister down there for years. Well more or less - well, more or less she's come round as a - as a friend and look after the hou
se a bit if mother was indisposed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And look after the rest of the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And when she got too old to do it she had to go into the workhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, yes, she -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well yes
, more or less in the family circle round here, mother come - there was ten children on each side, mother's and fathers and the brothers and sisters and they was all married in the farming line, and more or less connected with farming most of all of 'em w
as connected with farming, it's only one or two was connected with the - there was two of our cousins connected with the shipping - they was - masters on the - the St Mawes boats, called from Jenkins was called from - Falmouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 St Mawes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would they visit very often then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 It was a long way off then wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well yes. And then - mother - mother's younger sister, next to the youngest one, she marry a fellow from London used to look after the - house - rents and - 
places in London, make - collecting rents and that. Agent you know. But the most of the others, their family, the brothers and sisters - sister-in-laws always more or less marr - attached to the farming community.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they see much of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes,
 yes. That's where those feasts used to be very popular 'cos we used to have a lot of cousins and - I remember - remember reckoning up mother saying one day, sit there reckon up - me - I was eldest of sixty grandchildren so - you can just imagine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you did have a lot of cousins then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. And that was - lots more after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They would visit you and you would visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Was nothing you consider go down to St - St - to Pen - Penberth down Bethsehen farm and have a great big
 table down there perhaps fifty - up to thirty or forty - you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Down at Penberth cove that would be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Mm. Beshehan Farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What's the name of the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Bocen. Bocen. Bocen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was a big farm and your cousins lived there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, some of them and mother's sister, yes. Yes. Grover Farm was another place near St Agnes. Gover Farm. Yes. Another one was Tredinny Farm where the Warrens lived - two families. And - Gerwin Farm at St Just.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your parents have friends apart from relatives?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - no, well yes I suppose they did more or less, yes, they did have - friends.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where did they see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they more or less meet them in - in - when they go to chapel or go - or go Penzance market they s
ay well I seen so and so today and so and so or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 See them in market or in chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. 'Cos my - mother's - distant cousin used to play - the organ down at St - St. - Sennen church, that's - in the family like. She - she played up to the time of her death. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did mother and father share the same friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - some - more or less - I think not altogether the same I wouldn't say, not -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Father would have some men friends I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes, something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did mother have friends of her own apart from the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I don't know, I should say, not particularly definitely, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were friends ever invited into the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Very often?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well no, not very often I couldn't say, no, it was quite a change to see people come in like, we didn't have them in every day like some -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 If they happened to be passing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, yes, they'd come in and see you sometimes - more from - Australia 'cos we had cousins in Australia and different places and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They would be invited to take a meal would they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there any special days or occasions when friends visited?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well only on feast or - or Christmas time or - yes. There used to be - make a thrashing day
 when the - they get the local thrashing machine come in, 'cos that used to be done then with - a - a - a transport engine used to be portable, they used to be pulled with horses then in those days. When the thrash
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you say that the friends invited in were your mother's friends or father's friends, or both of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well the both I - be more or less - they more or less be - sister-in-laws or - brother-in-laws like they come down, they always come - rally round when we got - thrashing time, to give a bit of hand like - outdoors and indoors for the food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 A busy time with the harvest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Then usually used to have a piece of meat a roasting generally, and have a nice - vegetables, plenty of vegetables and all that you know. Boil up so
me Christmas - pudding like, the dark pudding or something, rice with it if you wanted to, always plenty of milk, rice pudding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did friends call in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, generally of a Sunday they'd come up - come up on Sunday after they've done their evening milking or done their farm}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11809502\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
work they come in around to have a chat and - see how - got out and have - sometime they go out and have a look around the farm, just to see what things was looking like. They're always interested a
nd - I know out to - ST Agnes uncle - out there well they had quite a biggish farm and - he nearly walked your legs off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They liked to walk around the place?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be relations would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well more or less relations, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would neighbours tend to do that as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - no, the - you always - neighbours are pretty friendly but - lend you a horse of - you know, if it was - if - if - other one indisposed or wanted assistance sometime or something like that b
ut - you don't - they didn't - more or less - visit very much like you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Didn't make a habit of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Only if they needed help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your parents ever go out to visit friends or neighbours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they went away jus
t - similar way to see - visit their friends, you know, go round the farm too and - sometimes we - we had - rabbits or anywhere like that they used to go out what we call have a bit days hunting like you know, and the rabbit shooting and - sometimes they 
used to go out - occasionally once a year or about twice a year for - where there was a lot of blackberries, go blackberry picking or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 All together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would all the family go, mother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - most would go
 like - be generally one or two home looking after the things and keeping an eye on them and - helping to get - stock in and - that's what I mean the animals and - see they were fed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusemen
ts, what do you think your parents did together with friends and neighbours with regard to amusements?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well, we never seen 'em - have any - amusement parties call - what you call 'em be more or less sit down and have a chat you know. About old Cornish - cup of tea and -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about music or games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, no, they never seen much of that, not a lot, unless anyone had a musical instrument in the house they might, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mother played the American organ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that be just to the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well that was only just for the family like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 There wouldn't be any games outside like cricket?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Or marbles or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Many people divide society into different social classes o
r groups, in that time before 1918 did you think of some people belonging to one and some to another of these classes or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - I don't think there's - much of that. You'd have the - well in religion like you'd have the Wesleyan and United Me
thodist and - and the church what we call - the old Salvation Army was very - very popular always in Cornwall, you always}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11809502\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
hear them - especially I used to enjoy them - up the Square at Camborne Saturday - Sunday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be religious differences?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there any class difference when you were a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Most people were much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you think they would all be described as working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well we'd be classed as a f
arming and fishermen and - after that they - well then the - the ordinary labourer, like farm labourers be classed a bit different.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would consider farm labourers as slightly lower class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well slightly lower yes, you would do, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would feel that you belonged in a group slightly above the farm labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Can you think of any groups that you would consider as above your farming folk and fishermen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - landlords - a lot of - a lot of - landlords down near 
- they used to own the ground, own the farms and all that sort of thing like - we were talking about Lord Robartes and all those pieces and - and - I didn't know who owned the ground - ground more or less down Penzance, we more - Bolitho's I think had qui
t
e a bit of - ground you know say down there. Bolitho's was noted family you know. And they was kind of - they used to do the - go out with the - hunting, run the hounds for some places you know, run - like Sir William Scorrier and - and Bolitho's and that
 and they more or less attached to a - an higher - grade of people like we call - gentry, they more or less had their - parties then and - hunting, you know, the - fox hunting - fox hunt and this like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would they be what we would call the landed gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 With large estates?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, large estates.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But there wouldn't be any group between your own farming and the landed gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were you ever told to touch your cap or show respect in some way to anyone?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Oh yes, especially - that type of people coming onto your place, the likes of the landlord came in or - or any lady or gentleman that was reall
y - coming, I mean you were always - told to - touch your cap. And - most - I - I noticed it that - that - even the lower class, what we call the working class - they - they - if they came into a gentleman's place - the front door to speak to the lady or 
gentleman they always take off their hat, I always notice them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be for the landed gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was there anyone that you yourself called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, no, not - no, not as a boy, no. It's only when the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you remember anyone showing respect in this way to your parents, like calling them sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well the - the - I think there's always a kind of respect of touching the hat and all that sort of thing. I know uncle used to even - raise his hat w
hen he was passing a - a - after - when the war was over, the - the - the - the war memorials or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He would raise his hat when he was passing the war memorial?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mm. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was a mark of respect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 In the village at St Buryan and at St Just who would have been considered the most important people? Was there any distinction at all?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - some of the leading grocery people or something like that and - perhaps the local council - officials we - more or less look up to.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that be the local council official on the West Penworth District Council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, yes, and - yes, or the - larger type of - business people like groceries people or the - the - with the implements and farming - you know, all that sort of - manure and all - business people, even in - boot shops in the big shops in town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Why would you think these business people were considered more important?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I don't know - exactly -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would it be because they had more money than the people who were working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well yes, I would think that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Live in a better style?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well, yes, we were always kind of - a better way of going on in life if you understand, from the ordinary - mining people and - labourers and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you come in contact with them very much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I didn't - I didn't do much of - business line or the shopping line.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about the clergy, who would they associate with as equals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I don't know, the - we didn't used to see a lot of them
 at all, like the - visit you and they didn't - I don't think they do so much visiting in those days somehow, I - they was more or less a - a parson and a - for - attend to your needs like the christening and - burying and marrying and - and - but farther
 than that well - I don't think they used to - contact them very much or see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you think they would visit any of the local people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I think they used to do - they'd come round to see 'em if they was very sick I suppose, if they knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 As a pastoral visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about teachers, who would they associate with as friends and equals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they was more or less sent - what we call the happy go lucky friends like they always very - friendly if you see them anywhere and p
erhaps meet them and talk about the children, mother, you know, ask how they're getting on at school or - something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Very informal and friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there any other employers in your area but farmers?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, well quarrying was - down at the Newland quarries, quarrying for stone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you know anything of the employers in that industry, or were they people who didn't actually live in the area?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well they didn't actually didn't live there in the areas, that's
 more or less the - was in - when the latter part after I got older I went down to the quarries to work in - in the wartime in the second world war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What sort of people would you say went to church? And to chapel. Was there any difference?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I
 think the general - public, the general people were - farmers and - and even the - people - I know - I know Illogan church the Bassett family from the - they used to have a big estate, At Tehidy - they had special pews for their - employees and all that.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be the landed gentry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about chapel, would the same type of people attend chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - no, they was more or less all together like. We would -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The same status?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would have - a certain amount of
 other - moneyed people like they would have their own pews and - own numbered pews but their - 'cos the other - people had to take more or less pot luck what we call it you know what I mean, they come in the church or chapel, they was always conducted to
 a seat generally with - by somebody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did the people who went to chapel, the moneyed people as you say, would they pay anything for their pew?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Oh yes. Pew rents, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was in chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did the same thing apply to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, it didn't, all church - it was generally free. Yes. Yes. They more or less had their own seat at - most people - claim there own part.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 By general usage they went in the same seat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But in chapel they paid rent and occupied that special seat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That particular pew, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would there have been any free seats?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes, there's free seats put down - in - in - towards the front, always a notice put up free seats on the side of the pew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 This was in chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. That was put up in a chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Where you lived did all the people in the working class have the same standard of living, or would you say that there were different groups within the working class, some having a better standard of living than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No, I don't think they did really, not as - as such as it is now these days. I think they more or less they - just ordinary living and - and they didn't have so much fancy and - sort of things as we get these days, it's more or less the home made - and -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there many mine workers in the area where you lived at St Buryan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - near - St Just more so. Been digging the Levant mines. I can always remember the Levant mine and - because I had a cousin there and was
 at the Levant - disaster when the man engine broke away, it was a man - it's a - the - the big - kind of a rod that men would ride on, they'd be lift up so many feet every time and - it broke away and several people was killed and injured.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was when you lived at St Just?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What age did you tell me you were when you moved to St Buryan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Eight. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you moved from St Buryan?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I was about fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So in 1911 you would have been at St Buryan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you think that any group felt itself superior to the rest in your society as a boy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I - I wouldn't say - in the - the Cornish way of going on that - that it was very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11809502\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 much distinction that way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Only these landowners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Who didn't live amongst you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were some families thought of as rough and others as more respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, there was - used to have one or two of the locals there - used to know down - down - the boys and that, they used to be
 a bit on the rougher side. Always noted for being a bit roughish like. But - we didn't used to get the vandalism now and all that - I don't think now, but - we never get very much trouble like more or less the - they were just a bit rough in their nature
, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you remember a distinction between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No, not really, but you always looked up to a good tradesman - they was always notified for their - carts - doing the carts or wagons or shoeing or - good carpenters a
lways known as a good carpenter and - I think they were always very - always very good tradesmen those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They'd have a certain distinction by being a craftsman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes. Quarrying and stone cutting and all that, monumental mason work and all that, used to all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They would have to serve an apprenticeship for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes, more or less. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And earn more money when they were qualified?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When they qualified. They - they - apprenticeship was very very - bad you know for the pay you get, very - very small. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They had very little pay when they were learning their craft?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes. 'Cos - you get - now, likes of Holman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11809502\charrsid11542501 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 s and these big - big firms, they - have an apprenticeship now and they're - brought on and they have a different salary.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Paid at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Which they weren't when you were a lad?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, yes, I
 think so because - yet - on farms on the general average - you didn't - have - many callers, like - sometimes now more or less they let of com - trave}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11809502\charrsid11542501 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 lers now, different now - dealing with fertilizers and - these kind of stuff, farm implements now - and 
- it's got on to - higher pitch now than when - when we was going along because they were just going along with their ordinary - just get a bit of manure or occasionally and - perhaps seeds for - the grass seed and all that sort of thing which you get in 
Penzance from HDP or the local - people who are agents for it, so you didn't get a lot of callers actually.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Done on a smaller scale with local people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class or group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, they didn't - they wasn't in a - a - in the financial - to - position to - to own their own farm and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They lived on a rented farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Her position as the daughter of the lighthouse keeper, would that give her any special class?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No. No, not really, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Actually there was very little class grouping in your environment at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, that's right, you - you wouldn't notice it at all hardly because -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you remember anyone within your locality being described as a real lady or a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - one or two occasionally - I should say the landlord again - Mr Hrvey and - at Sennen who was landlord of the - one or two farms round there I used to know and - Mr Boyas - used to be the local farme
r there, I used to know him, he was a kind of a gentleman farmer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He had a big farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. But - we always look up to some of these here bigger farmers as - well gentlemen - gentlemen farmers. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And that would be by reason of their ownership of the land and a little more money as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And employing of labour. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Occasionally. I remember once that - my father give - his - sister-in-law or sis
ter a ride on a - on the road and a policeman happened to see 'em - see her and he came down our place to look for - whether he had a licence for carrying anybody. And he couldn't find it, eventually I found it for him - in some papers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Gave a ride in the trap?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
She give the - his sister - his sister or sister-in-law, I can't remember some - I forget - a ride, you know, with - him on the road and he was seen giving her a ride you see and - he wanted the - the policeman came around to see whether h
e had a - a traffic lic - a - a - a trap licence we used to call it in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you were naughty did your mother ever say, I'll call a policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What did you think of the policeman yourself as a lad?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well a more - treat them more or less respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He lived in the village did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Generally. They'd only come round occasionally to see your licence sometimes and, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Make sure you had a gun licence?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, or some - or something like that.
 I don't remember see the other licence now - which - 'cos there wasn't trouble much licence in those days like car licence and that. You know, I didn't know you had to keep records in those days somehow, I don't think you did somehow, moving of cattle or
 -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How do you think the policeman treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well they was more or less a friendly bobby like used to keep an eye and - keep an eye on the boys sometimes and I think that's what used to keep them in order because the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Like a good neighbour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I think you told me your home was rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Who was your landlord when you were at St Just?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - they used to pay the rent into the Barclays Bank but I just forget who the landlord was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The landlord was}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 abse}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 t?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you have any feelings about him as a landlord or any knowledge of him at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. But when we went to St Buryan - Mr Hosken - he was a - owner then of 
the land, and - but he used to run a local - another farm besides and - we used to - used to meet him at chapel and that and then we'd go St Buryan chapel, he was rather - friendly - neighbour.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mr Hosken was a gentleman farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And he owned the farm that your father rented?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 This Mr - yes, and - yes. He was no relation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh always did really. Yes. There was always a - hard - days in those d
ays, and you had to bring on young cattle and you bring them on with your - your own milk very often, you buy a little bit of what we call Bibby's cakes sometimes, bring on to help the calf rearing. I remember - I remember father reading three calves spec
ially on Bibby's cake and that and brought them on and then he went out on the - kind of a damp autumn weather on what we call the - damp ground and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501 they got what we call the fillun}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 , then lost the three of them. It come as a terrible blow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be a great financial loss wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you yourself think anything about your parents struggle to make ends meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes, I think we - we didn't have a lot of money to waste, we were never given a lot of money to waste.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You knew you all had to pull your weight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What difference did it make to the family if your father was ill, do you ever remember your father being ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not really, not really seriously ill, no, I - I don't remember him having a
n accident of any kind, not to - I've - he's had a cold probably been sick or some - we've had to go and - help, get on a bit, but I never - I don't think I've ever seen father what I call seriously ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Nor out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you recall any knowledge of anyone in the parish having help from the Guardians or Parish charity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Not in those days. No. That occurred more or less after we came up to - Treloweth, when we was on the milk round, used to get the relief then, they get the bread 
and the - the van come round then with a van with a loaf of bread, and - you'd get a - a ticket for the milk, a pint of milk a day or something like that, that was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But not while you were a youngster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Now when I was a youngster. I - I was going
 to - excuse me - I was going to say - in those days - if anyone was really sick, we had to go out and perhaps the wives would - if the husband was sick, like the farm labourer, they'd have to go out perhaps and help on the farm a bit, perhaps do some was
hing or - do a - perhaps help on the crops or - like - something like that, help out. They had to go out and do a bit of washing or something like that, 'cos you couldn't get no other relief those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 With a family business you would all do a bit extra, if the father was poorly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
When there was someone in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly, was there any special way in which they showed it? Do you remember anyone being thought to be a nuisance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Nobody being drummed out of the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No. No. No. Be all - type at St Buryan and that, they - and - and even up to St Just there, the Saturdays nights they - after pay days they used to have a quite a - beer was quite cheap in those days, a
bout tuppence an pint and - they used to have a fight, some generally have a fight before they come home, what my father said on the Saturday night at St Buryan you know, a fight but - I don't think they got into very serious trouble but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be more like an equal fight and not by a lot of people picking on one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Oh no, no, they stand around a ring you see and the two would get in the ring and fight - fight it out what the - the argument was about. And - I've heard father say once that - t
he - as the fellow's come round they had a bit of grudge against 'em well somebody else would give 'em a tap under the ribs when he got a change so - throw a blow in you know from the ringside.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But never anybody being drummed out of the place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How many acres was Bosavern Farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 About ten I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
You mentioned that your mother used to wash in a crock over a furze bush fire, this was probably in a furnace, would that have been what you meant?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well yes I think it would be - we have an old boiler like thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 A copper would it be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well it be called - unless now - I know - remember after we used to get a copper built in bricks in the corner like and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was it built in then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I think this one we used t
o remember - if I remember be out doors or out - out of doors in the corner of the yard somewhere and they fed it with stick or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How was it fixed, was it held on a tripod?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh it was - kind of a - three legs like on a iron - or - or - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you could build up a furze fire under it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I couldn't see how the furze could have heated an indoor furnace.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So later you had the indoor one which was called a furnace and was built in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Built in, and also then you - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And a wooden cover?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Wod - wooden cover. Well then that was fed by more or less - fed with coal sometime but they used to go out pick sticks you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Any fuel that you had you could use?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right. That's right. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The lady who came round to do your sewing, did she carry her own sewing machine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Yes, generally, I don't think - my - my - I believe mother did have a sewing machine after - after a year or two but - I think that - in the beginning I think they did rely on the lady coming.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 She was a Miss Osborn, not married you said didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you say she was a crippled lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You said that when you killed a pig on the farm something there would be pudding skins, would mother stuff these herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
They'd be washed them through with water, jugs or tap, I think we used to have a jug - and then wash them out you know and clean them and then they'd be boiled in salt and - be stuffed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What were they stuffed with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, breadcrumbs and more or less something and a bit of spices or something like that I suppose, but - tasty, but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What we call hogs pudding now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. I don't think there'd be any vegetables put in the - skins.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were saying about the chickens and feeding them, I presume as a farmer you would have sold eggs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well yes, they would - clean them, well we'd have - that would be our job really to - specially towards to the Thursday when they was going to be taken to market, surplus eggs, would be to wash them and - put them in - grade them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be one of your little duties as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Wash the eggs. And then sometimes we were helping in the house for to do clean the bright - spoons
 or knives or the - you would have an old board then - with the - brick and a bit of - rubbed them on you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When we were talking about concerts at the chapel, I'm not sure if you said there were special Peace Concerts or special Feast concerts.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well Feast concert, Feast.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The St Just Feast and so on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Yes. You get the anni - what they call the Sunday school anniversary and all - sort of thing. I was - that's was more - they used to get them I think occasionally then Harvest Fes
tivals I think we used to remember having Harvest Festivals, they - they - they seemed more proper the latter years than - I remember more about them the latter years, the Harvest Festivals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Special times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Special church festivals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
This Mary Trewavas who came to look after your mother when she had the children were born and she died in the work house you said, which work house would that have been?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Madran. It's near Penzance.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was the nearest one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were you given lessons by one of your parents or by any other tutors at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh about five years old. I should think, I think at five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What time of the morning did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well they used to - well about - St Just would be about a mile walk? I was leaving home about half past eight I suppose, and - St Buryan be a mile and a half - probably was - might be quarter past eight or - just after then.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The school started at nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, at nine o'clock. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When did you come back then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
We came back in the evening, we didn't often - came back, we used to have - a small - money then, tuppence or something to buy a bit of dinner at the local shop, a few bi
scuits from the baker that'd come round. But we didn't have any canteen dinners those times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you stayed at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, take a bit of lunch probably, took a sandwich or two or perhaps. I don't know if there was any means of getting your pasty
 warm or anything in those days - then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You didn't carry lunch with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 O}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501 c}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 ca}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
ion - we may have carried some - something we could eat sometimes, a bit of cake and - you know, bread and cake and - bread and butter something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What kind of school was it that you attended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The ordinary -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 The ordinary Board school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Was this a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did it cater for the full range, five to fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Five to fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How did you get to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Walked. Yes. No transport in those -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How long did it take you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well about - well - we could say about twenty minutes - half an hour.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did anyone go with you when you went to school first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, we had to find our own way there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where did you have your midday meal then when you were at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I - think we had a kind of a lobby like a thing but was no special canteen room nor - no - no - meal room I can remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You could sit in the lobby on a form?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, probably, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What did you have to eat, lunch you took with you or bought?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Lunch generally we take sandwiches or - or something like that and - might buy a few biscuit in the local shop - or something li
ke that. There was no chip shops or anything of that in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well I used to like it very much, used to like going to school, I got on very well at school. I think I was in the ex-seven for two week or - what we call the ex-seven in those days, before I took my exam to leave school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How did you feel about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well the - Master Rowe and - used to - was our - at St Levan school I - I don't remember the - the teachers much when I was young - b
eing younger at St Just.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were they men or women?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - the man teacher that I more or less remember about, and there was Mr Stone at St Buryan where I took my exam that time you know, the man teacher.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as being important in life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well yes, we was - more or less drilled into - kind of good behaviour like and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they teach you anything about punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well punctuality was more or less the - point that - that you - you was regular at school and regular at leaving night time.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They'd expect it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would they teach you ways of speaking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not particularly, I don't - we didn't get - that, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No elocution?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about manners or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well the - that was all more - pretty well general, I - I think the schools used to - kept - a little bit - I think they used to be tidier really round than they are now, they seem to be -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Generally have to stand in the corner or something like that. You may - you would - would get the cane in those days. Yes. I've seen boys have the cane, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you may have to stand in the corner or get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were the girls treated the same as the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - I don't know that - the girls were so rough in those days as the boys -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How about punishment, would they get the same punishment as the boys if they were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I think they would - yes, if they really - were naughty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They'd get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And stand in the corner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What particular offences would this be for in school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, not doing their work properly or - or talking in - talking - in - in class or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your parents show any interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes, yes. They - father and mother both of them really I think used to - if not very educated but they used to - like to - interested.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No. Didn't get the - the home - open day like they used - later on, now they get a - school - parents are invited to school to see work, but I don't think ever remember that - being - happening in my day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They were completely separate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they ever meet the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. Not that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 They wouldn't have met them in the street or at chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did the other children at school come from similar types of home to your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - there was kind - mixed if you understand - there used to be farming and - fishing - I can remember the -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But the standard of the home would be similar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Similar.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not on grounds of some children being dressed better or some children being brighter than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, no, I - that - that didn't seem to - cut any figure at all, not - when I was going to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there any gangs or groups in the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No, not - I could say that. But I remember - being - told off by the school master once by - we was out - in the dinner hour and we got a bit rough like I suppose between on
e and other and I tore another boy's shirt or colar or something or just disrupt his uniform or what - what it was and - he - he got - I got told off, he said, I think you ought to know better than that you know, and he - didn't expect me to do such thing
s, or something like that. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You didn't have any punishment for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. no, no, just told -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Just told you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No - we didn't have any - special - anybody specially in to assist anyone who was a bit backward - we had to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Everybody was treated fairly you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Your first school was at St Just and then you went on to St Buryan when you moved there to live?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Those were the only two schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were eight years old when you went to St Buryan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. At St Just if I remember rightly we had a dividing wall between the boys and the girls, that's the - younger ones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So it wasn't a mixed school as such?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right. But I - I - at St Levan it was more or less one yard and - and - and real - really mixed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 In classes there were boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right, yes, proper mixed school there. Most likely have been more teachers - I -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Headmistress and headmaster?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's right, I think, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you have stayed longer if you had had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well I suppose I would have put me time out to fourteen if - but th
en - the - I was wanted more or less home on the farm and father - being - pretty advanced in education and couldn't go any further there so I came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were able to leaver earlier than the full range to fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Through taking ex - a - a labour exam what we call in those days for - for going to work if you wanted to. You'd have to take an exam. You couldn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And if you passed it you could leave at thirteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did that apply to children who wanted to work anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
The factory, one of the boys - one of the girls - we was two boys that really took it, and - one went to the local milk factory to work and I went on the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So any children could take that exam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well, when you look around you say yes because - you think you've been working all your life and - you've never got anywhere by - hard work can get - you know - making very much, you don't get very f
ar in life being home on the farm working but - but now with the modern machinery and all that you've really got to have an education for - dealing with - with the farm and generally on cattle and everything and you've got to be - you've got to have a fai
rly decent education now because - even a farm labourer really got to be fair - more or less more efficient now, because they've got machinery and - bet - better class cattle now and - it's graded now different and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you attend any part time education after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No. No, no - no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I was always on the farm like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were needed at home to do your part time work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I should like to ask you about your first full time job, what was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, working on the farm generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 At home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 With your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. But when I came to Pool, I went to - helped to - with a cattle drover on -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you left school at fourteen that was when you moved from St Buryan to Nancekuke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Nancekuke. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So your first work was with your father on the farm at Nancekuke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. And - and Bosanketh. At - at St - well - well I was at - and St Buryan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you had a year working at St Buryan before you moved to Nancekuke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What exactly did you have to do in this job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, always done
 the - horses in those days and used to - use the - I didn't remember doing a lot of ploughing but I used to do the - breaking down of the ground with the implements, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Milking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Milking and general like that. Perhaps help to assist and - wit
h doing fences, hedges and all that. And well assisted the harvesting and all that, building the loads because - you get a - perhaps a man come in or - father and then there'd be - if you wasn't able to do the heavy - lifting there with fork - forks or pi
kes what they used in those days well you could build - get up and right away the load like you would call.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What was a pike used for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well that's for lifting the hay you know for - used to get -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How many prongs would a pike have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Two. Have two. Two prongs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What would you call an evil?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
That'd be a fork - a four or five. Five, might be up to six, but they used to use the - find that the four was a pretty handy tool for - handling manure and spreading it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So that would be what an evil would be used for as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. A dung fork we used to call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What hours did you normally work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - we used to try and get away though say probably get out about seven in the mornings generally I think and then you carry o
n then with the milking and general cleaning up. Father used to - do remember take away the - milk cans in a cart - horse and cart. And - then we -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Take them and sell the milk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be taken to a creamery, yes, and then - they'd have to b
e - I don't know they was cleaned with steam, I don't know - think they was, I think they had to be more or less clean when you bring 'em back the cans, the empty cans, they would be tipped into a -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So father took the milk away in the churns, was anything else done with the milk besides taking to the creamery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well sometimes used a separator and - and separated the milk from cream, and used the milk sometimes for - pigs, and the cream would be used then as - as scalded cream or - for making butte
r. But then - that was the more or less at - more - I can remember about when I was at St Just when - they used to have a proper churn to put the cream in then, and then they used to milk the - cream would be - took off the milk, leave it to settle and ta
k
e off the cream. And then placed into a kind of a churn - which revolves and then - after it turned to butter, it would be sold to - and made up in little plays like. And that used to be taken to the market - taken to Penzance market or anywhere - or the 
local people - shops. They may have been agents for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What time would you be able to leave work on a normal working day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well there was no - fixed time, but - once we had finished our work we were more or less - we didn't - work on not unless
 it was a harvest time we used to have a bit of leisure time that you could - do a bit of reading or bit of - running around or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be after milking normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. That's right. Sometimes we had to clean a harness or polish a trap and p
olish the lamps or - for the - for the - that's for what they used to use for the - market or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Get the trap ready for market next day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well that was a day of just ordinary work, we never use
d to do any farming in those days as - I don't think they used to do so much on the - the crops or - farm in those days at all, it was more or less kept as the - Sunday. You just do the - the milking and - looking after the cattle and - and barring that i
t would be - nothing else extra, it was never encouraged - Sunday working - well Sunday working in those days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What about Saturday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well that was more or less the same as the ordinary day, didn't do much distinction that way. I think one or two 
of the local boys probably that couldn't do - that had brothers and that and they could get off used to sometimes have little cricket matches. Used to be very popular.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was at St Buryan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Ah yes, and St Just round that's all. They're - they're still noted as - as good footballers and cricketers down there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you play cricket then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I didn't much, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you have any half day off on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No, no, no time off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No holidays I suppose at that stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No, we used to go to our - perhaps a neighbour or - uncle and auntie for - for a day or a couple of days sometimes, or go - or - occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would be when the farm work was slack?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When was slack, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you have any holidays with pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What were you paid when you started to work first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well was no general payment - we didn't have any - well - well acknowledged general payment then - you - you - your - you'd have a little bit of pocket money, and - that was all I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Half a crown a week or something like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Something like that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Or less probably?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Sometimes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you feel that that was fair or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, we - we were - must take it because that was all that - we - we - we knew that we didn't have a lot of money to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was the way of life?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. I remember from - if granny or somebody - when we go to a tea treat or anything like that granny gave you tuppence or something, 
said mind you didn't spend it all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Granny would give you a few coppers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You only worked with your own family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you would get on with them all right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And your employer was your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How did you get on with him as an employer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 All right. Yes, worked well - yes, comfortable - he used to try and - bring us on, teach us - what we should do and how it should be done.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 He really taught you about farming and the care of the land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Time of seeding and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you enjoy the work?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. As - when the - as different crops were coming in rotation you'd have potatoes, you put them about to sit - what we call 'em, let 'em shoot, and then - keep them - away from - 
too dark a light otherwise they shoot too much you know, and then - we'd have corn, we'd have - the old fashioned days used to have a - a winding machine in the farm and wind out the - the - this - seed - the - the - anything like sort of - what do you ca
ll it, charlick seed and all that, used to be - do a winding machine and you'd have - be opposite doors like and the draught of the wind would carry any light - corn or any light - you never used to use the best seed you see for the corn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would blow the chaff away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did working alter your attitude to school at all? You didn't wish you were back at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were quite happy working?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 From the time of leaving school at thirteen you worked with your 
father on the farm. How long did you continue being employed by your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Oh right on to - after we - gived up the farm and went to dairy farm and milk we - we went on to milk retailing, carrying our milk around in buckets, cans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you would have received a wage then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well yes. Well yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that be right up to the time that you were married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And you were married in 1934 was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. You see, in those days - when you was working on a farm we didn't have
 a lot of wages but - when - more or less the fathers, most of the - sons going in for farming they'd try and help them to start a farm and give 'em something to start off with like cattle and all that, so you would have more or less that I mean as - some
times you'd have a bit of money, sometimes give to you to save but - on the general average you would find that - farmers us to try and set their farm - up - sons on a farm if they could you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Rather than pay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - that's the general - acknowledgement like they used to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would live on the farm and the living would be free, just as if you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would have pocket money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 But there would come a time when you would have to be paid a man's wage wouldn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes. Yes. Yes. If you was - if you was - going to be - that way, or going - going to be married and work on - still work on the farm as a - part - time, still, you - you'd have a wage then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were working on the farm in that way when you were first married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I was working as a single man.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Can you remember when you ceased to work on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you left the farm to work somewhere else, when was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - not actually before - I went to - I got married actually, I finished the farm then. Then I runned a chip shop then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was in 1934?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Then you had some capital to start a chip shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How long did you have the chip shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 About twelve year I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So 1934 to 1946?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes, that's about it, that's right, 'cos I went to - Newlyn Quarries to work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That would have included the second world war period wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Oh - yes, that's right, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you had the chip shop did you start to do another job as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well w - I did use a - a lor - a - a lorry to a bit of lightly - re - reta}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501 il}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501  works of - in the - in addition to a bit of a coal round, did a bit of a coal round. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You had a lorry and carried coal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When was that from about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well 1940 I should say round.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was just after the war began?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 And how long did you continue to do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Until - in the - in the second world war well then I went down to - I had to do something extra like, and I went to the quarries to work.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Newlyn. Yes, then I was a - I learnt excavating driving and I was driving big lorries, taking them to Nancekuke and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 What year do you think that started, when you took on this job at the quarry? Immediately the war began or would it have been 1940/41?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well it was in the world war because - I remember the aeroplanes coming over and dropping bombs at Newlyn.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you took on this full time job then as an excavator driver for Newlyn Quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That's the stone quarry?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you continue to have the chip shop then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I finished it. Owing to the death of my first wife.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Your first wife died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 193 - 1941. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So then you continued until the end of the war to work at the Newlyn quarry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would that be 'til 1945 or 6?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, roughly that, I think it's about that - '46 that I got - a lorry that was working there,
 I bought the lorry from the fellow and he went to Birmingham to - go on taxi work, and - I came up to - back to this way to live - to - from - from lodgings again more or less what you might say, to - get a contract with the Urban District Council which 
I carried on for twenty years then as a local contractor, a self-employed - local contractor under the Camborne Redruth Urban District Council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 That was doing haulage work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Which I continued up to my - retirement.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you have preferred any other type of occupation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Not really, I enjoyed it really, 'cos I had a change really from the farming and - I think that - I got on with the - job very well - he was very well pleased, I had a nice letter from the - council when I finished and I never had no trouble and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 At one stage did you cease to be self-employed and be employed by the council?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Always con - always contract, always self - I was always self - self-employed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 On Contract work for the ......
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Urban Di
strict Council. Yes. I think we used to charge at about, if I remember rightly about seven and six an hour - those days. But the charges went up gradually but not terribly heavy.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you serve an apprenticeship or training period for any of this work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
No, no, I didn't, no, I just took over a - the manager, when I drew up the first lorry at Penzance and Mr - the manager at - Newlyn Quarries came up and asked me if I'd take a - he said there was one down there that was outside Taylor's garage and 
I had to take it to Perrenporth, first time taking a big lorry. And I got on all right with it. And I continued because I was always used to driving and - never nothing heavy before but driving - light cars and all that sort of thing. 'Cos - I always been
 driving because when I took up Ambulance work and do a lot of driving for them and - I - I always took it up, I was rather interested because my cousin was one of the first drivers in Cornwall that went for private hire at St - Carbis Bay Hotel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 So you enjoyed driving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Any sort of vehicle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. And all the - and all the family have been in -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you belong to any trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Or professional organisation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you feel that employers and workers had the same interests or different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well - yes I think you did really but - I think they used to be more or less - more or less conscientious in those days of working, and used to try and - I think now the - well, you have to work in those days, 
if you understand, different to what you have now with the trade unions now well - I didn't know the - whether they've got the better end of the stick now and - have got - the - the employers haven't got sort of too much to say about it and that - as they
 used to. The farmers - and all these here employers now they've got to - give them holidays and all that, which I think is very nice. We don't want the old days back, when we had to work or starve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers themselves at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not so much as it is nowadays I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Some people say that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, like tradesmen, did you feel that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - I -
 I think it was really sometimes a bit - in those days - if a - a - a tradesman didn't like another tradesman you - well - another man of another trade interfering with what he was doing in his trade, he did - they more or less liked to keep their trade s
eparate, not be - not a plumber coming in doing a carpenter's job or something like that, you know, they - I think they used to have a distinction in their trades that they liked to keep to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 There was no social distinction?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Not social, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Between being a craftsman or a tradesman and a labourer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well you had a bit more incentive I think of - getting - trying to make a better living, a better standard of - living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you continue to live at home after you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did starting work full time change your relationships with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, I don't think so, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 With brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, no, we all -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you spend your Sundays any differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well no. I used to attend church quite regularly after I got married.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you go to Sunday school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I used to when I was younger, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 After you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well no, I didn't - I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Too busy on the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you take any interest in politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How did you spend any spare time you had after the farm work was done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well if it was then - no - no preparation of - for 
the Penzance Market in the way of cleaning harness or - cleaning the - vehicle, probably would go out - perhaps in the season picking blackberries or go out and - with father in the evening stalking a few rabbits around that come out in the evenings for }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501 grazing}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 , something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You would shoot the rabbits then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You said earlier that you would save skins from the rabbits, what would be done with those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - I - I used to - I don't know that we used to use 
them very much, I think we used to get about penny or tuppence each, it wasn't very much then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You could sell them,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Sell them, they'd take them - there'd - I believe a fellow used to come round and buy them, buy them and - buy jam jars or buy rabbit}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13397530\charrsid11542501 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
skins and - I don't know, they used to take them to Penzance for disposal but I think used to - probably used to come round occasionally and - buy them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 After you left St Buryan when you were fourteen and you came to Nancekuke and then to Pool, 
did that make any difference to your evenings or spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Yes, I think we used to get out for a bit more walk then, you had a bit more to see, you go out round look at the local landscape and mining and all around and - then I took interest in - i
n the local Ambulance so that took up what quite a bit of my time, I took up music too a bit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 This was when you lived at Pool?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 When you were fifteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were able to go out in the evenings a bit then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where to, to the Ambulance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. I - I got a cycle after a year or two and - I used to go a bit of cycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You joined the St John's Ambulance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, St John's, yes, 'cos I was there - been there for thirty year, I've got a long service medal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Who did you go with at that stage when you were a lad in your teens?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Well the local boys like there was more - boys around because then I think - going to the Ambulance and going to the - perhaps the - local Wesley Social we use
d to have and that we got more or less we teamed up with more youngsters 'cos there wasn't very many around when we - before we came on - to - round to the - occupied - more occupied places like, where we stood before was very quiet and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Country and this was the urban district?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Urban district.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you make any new friends, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Both boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How did you meet them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well - more or less - through - the Ambulance or the - going
 to the Wesley - what we call the Monday night's - Band of Hope and anything like that or a concert was going on, there would be more concerts about than - more - things to do, round here you see was the - two or three or chapels around, three or four cha
pels round, there isn't many chapels around where I didn't used to go to the harvest festivals or - anniversaries or something like that, used to go for - we used to go - like going like that and - go for a bit of walk after.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you ever bring friends home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Occasionally, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No. Not - really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 No, not then - not special - I mean nothing special like, we just -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Your own brother was not much younger than you, would he have been your friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, they used to - we used to go together 'cos - I remember - now -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Any special friends, boys or girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, well - we used to - brothers used to very - go together, we used to go to chapel and that, I rem
ember George came home from America and we was three of us, and we went up to - for Wesley, Mr Penberthy said they didn't very often see - see brothers going up along together ever like that you know. But - we was always a family that pulled together very
 well, we've always - brothers and sisters. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you make any friends among the local lads?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes. Yes, you did, yes, and - we used to know them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Where would you go with them? For walks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well, yes, and - to the general activities around like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Ambulance?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did your parents meet your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 
Oh yes, some of the times. Well one or two local chaps, yes, they'd come in, we have come in for supper in the evenings, used to come in and have - a bit of cold meat, you couldn't get that now off the joint after you've had Sunday dinner.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did they expect to know where you were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes, yes, they was very particular that, if you wasn't home and - weren't - been out anywhere and you - an
d you had to be home at a reasonable time and if you don't they would ask you why you're so late and that. There was more - strict on the girls too, they had to be in by nine.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 At what age were you when you married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 About twenty-nine wasn't I.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 How long had you known your wife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 I'd say about four year probably.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 She was a local girl was she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. We met more or less going to church or - going - local activities, attendant to - church. Tea treat or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Did you save up money before getting married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Well a little, yes, a little, yes. Did have a bit of help from my father and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Your parents helped you in setting up home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Well her parents helped - her, and my parents helped - to start off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Were there longer engagements in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes, very - two or three years generally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6778144 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 You were engaged about that long were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4475040 EH  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1389977\charrsid11542501 Yes. Yes.
\par }}